sentences: Danny de Graaf (born 30 March 1988, in Amsterdam), who performs under the stage name David Gravell, is a Dutch trance DJ and music producer.
David Gravell first gained recognition in 2013 for his original "Bulldozer", released on W&W's label Mainstage Music.
David Gravell's first ever release was his track "Downtown" on Visionair Records in 2010.
Between 2013 and 2015, he had well-received releases such as "Bulldozer", "Megatron', "Timebomb", "The Last Of Us" and "Supernova".
Within six months, his remix for Dash Berlin's 'Man On The Run' reached over 1 million plays on Spotify.
Meanwhile, Gravell has played at four A State Of Trance Festivals in Sydney, Ibiza and Utrecht.
